Health organizations recommend that people cover their mouth and nose with flexed elbow or a disposable cough or sneeze scarf, and discard the scarf immediately.
It is recommended that those who may be infected wear surgical masks, as the use of a mask can limit the volume and distance traveled by respiratory droplets that disperse when talking, sneezing, and coughing.
