The Government of South Korea achieved its capacity to conduct tests, mainly in private sector laboratories, over the course of several years.
On March 16, the World Health Organization called for increased testing programs as the best way to reduce the spread of the COVID-19 pandemic.The high demand for testing due to the widespread spread of the virus caused delays of hundreds of thousands of tests in private laboratories in the U.S., and supplies of isopads and chemical reagents were depleted.
